<h1> Insert Cross-References </h1> 

    <p> Cross-references link an object element to another page within the same document. </p>


<li>1. Locate the Cross-References panel. (Choose Window > Type & Tables > Cross-References.)</li>
<li>2. Select the point where you want to insert the cross-reference.
<li>3. Open the New Cross-Reference dialog box (Choose Window > Type & Tables > Cross-References, and then choose Insert Cross-Reference from the menu)</li>
    
<li>4. Choose Paragraph or Text Anchor from the Link To menu.</li>

<li>5. Select the document you want to reference, select paragraph style in the left box then select the paragraph. </li>
<li>6. Choose your cross-reference format from the Format menu.</li>

</html> 